[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA critical memory safety vulnerability has been detected in the FreeRDP codec [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimplementation during fuzzing. The issue manifests as an AddressSanitizer SEGV [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39msegmentation fault[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m caused by a wild write to an unknown memory address in the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rfx_process_message_metadata` function. The crash occurs after multiple failed [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclear codec decompression attempts, ultimately resulting in a write access [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mviolation at address `[0m[1;36m0x7f3e07b98e20[0m[39m`.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Vulnerability Type[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis is a **memory corruption vulnerability** specifically categorized as:[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **SEGV [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSegmentation Fault[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** caused by a WRITE memory access[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Wild-addr-write** with a scariness score of [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m, indicating an out-of-bounds or [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvalid memory write[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Potentially exploitable as it involves writing to memory outside of allocated [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboundaries[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Issue Details[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe crash occurs during the processing of RemoteFX codec data through the following[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecution path:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The fuzzer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TestFuzzCodecs`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m executes with [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m iterations on a test case[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Multiple errors occur in the Clear codec decompression phase:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `pixelIndex [0m[1;36m257[0m[39m != pixelCount [0m[1;36m1326[0m[39m` mismatch[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `pixelIndex [0m[1;36m257[0m[39m != pixelCount [0m[1;36m1536[0m[39m` mismatch  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `pixelIndex [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m + runLengthFactor [0m[1;36m193[0m[39m > pixelCount [0m[1;36m105[0m[39m` boundary violation[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All resulting in `clear_decompress_residual_data` and `clear_decompress` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfailures[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Subsequently, a SEGV occurs at `[0m[35m/src/FreeRDP/libfreerdp/codec/[0m[95mrfx.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m734:26[0m[39m` in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `rfx_process_message_metadata` function during a WRITE operation[0m                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbegins. This suggests possible shared state corruption or cascading failures.[0m       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Memory Write Violation**: The crash is caused by a WRITE operation attempting [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto access memory at an invalid address, indicating potential:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Buffer overflow[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Use of corrupted pointer[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Incorrect bounds checking[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Integer overflow leading to invalid memory calculations[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Location**: The crash occurs in `rfx_process_message_metadata` at line [0m[1;36m734[0m[39m, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcolumn [0m[1;36m26[0m[39m, suggesting a specific write operation at that location is using an [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvalid memory address.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Deduplication Token**: `DEDUP_TOKEN: [0m                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter examining the code snippets and evaluation report, I've identified a critical[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity vulnerability in the FreeRDP RemoteFX codec implementation. The issue is [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**malicious code that creates an arbitrary write primitive**, not a typical memory [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msafety bug.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Findings[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Malicious Code Components:**[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Global variables `metadataBlock` [0m[1;39m([0m[39minitialized to `&explicit_bzero`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`metadataData` at lines [0m[1;36m142[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m179[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Extra data reading in `rfx_process_message_frame_begin` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m674[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m680[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreads [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes beyond standard protocol[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `rfx_process_message_metadata` function [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m709[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m736[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that performs [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marbitrary memory write[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - WBT_METADATA case handler [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1319[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1322[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that triggers the exploit[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Exploit Mechanism:**[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Attacker sends FRAME_BEGIN with [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m extra bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mblockOffset + metadataData[0m[1;39m)[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - System calculates: `target_address = &explicit_bzero + blockOffset`[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Attacker sends METADATA block [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0xCCC8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to trigger write[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - System executes: `*[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmetadataBlock = metadataData` [0m[1;39m([0m[39marbitrary [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrite[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Evidence This Is Malicious:**[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Not part of MS-RDPRFX specification [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno TS_RFX_METADATA documented[0m[1;39m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No legitimate encoder writes metadata blocks[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Uses `&explicit_bzero` as ASLR bypass base[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Complete control over write address and data[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No legitimate functionality provided[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix requires **complete removal** of all malicious code components from the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minitial codebase. This is a removal-only patch as there is no legitimate [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality to preserve.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Remove Global Variables[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location:** `libfreerdp/codec/rfx.c`[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRemove the two global variable declarations:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m142[0m[39m: `UINT64 metadataBlock = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m&explicit_bzero;`[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Line [0m[1;36m179[0m[39m: `UINT64 metadataData = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThese variables are only used by the malicious code and have no other references in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe codebase.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Remove Extra Data Reading from Frame Begin[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location:** `libfreerdp/codec/rfx.[0m[1;92mc:674[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m680[0m[39m` in `rfx_process_message_frame_begin`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRemove the conditional block that reads extra data beyond the standard RFX [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprotocol:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mStream_GetRemainingLength[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m >= [0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    UINT64 blockOffset = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT64[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, blockOffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT64[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, metadataData[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    metadataBlock += blockOffset;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe function should only read the standard [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mframeIdx + numRegions[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m as per [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe legitimate encoder implementation at lines [0m[1;36m2154[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m2155[0m[39m.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m: Remove or Disable Metadata Message Handler[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location:** `libfreerdp/codec/rfx.[0m[1;92mc:709[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m736[0m[39m`[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOption A [0m[1;39m([0m[39mRecommended[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Remove the entire `rfx_process_message_metadata` function.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOption B [0m[1;39m([0m[39mConservative[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Replace the function body to reject metadata blocks:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstatic INLINE BOOL [0m[1;35mrfx_process_message_metadata[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRFX_CONTEXT* WINPR_RESTRICT [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontext,[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                               RFX_MESSAGE* WINPR_RESTRICT message,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                               wStream* WINPR_RESTRICT s,[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                               UINT16* WINPR_RESTRICT [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpExpectedBlockType[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext->priv[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mWLog_Print[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext->priv->log, WLOG_ERROR, [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[32m"WBT_METADATA blocks are not supported"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return FALSE;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m: Remove Metadata Case from Message Processing Switch[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location:** `libfreerdp/codec/rfx.[0m[1;92mc:1319[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1322[0m[39m` in `rfx_process_message` function[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRemove or disable the WBT_METADATA case:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOption A [0m[1;39m([0m[39mRecommended[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Remove the entire case block:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcase WBT_METADATA:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    ok = [0m[1;35mrfx_process_message_metadata[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext, message, subStream,[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                     &context->expectedDataBlockType[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    break;[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOption B [0m[1;39m([0m[39mConservative[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Replace with error handling:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcase WBT_METADATA:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mWLog_Print[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext->priv->log, WLOG_ERROR, [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[32m"WBT_METADATA blocks are not supported"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    ok = FALSE;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    break;[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m: Optional - Remove WBT_METADATA Constant[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location:** `libfreerdp/codec/rfx_constants.h:[0m[1;36m38[0m[39m`[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mConsider removing the constant definition:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#define WBT_METADATA [0m[1;36m0xCCC8[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHowever, this step is optional as the constant itself is harmless without the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39massociated handling code.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This is the Optimal Approach[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Complete Security Fix**: Removes all components of the arbitrary write exploit[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **No Legitimate Functionality Lost**: The code provides no legitimate RFX codec [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Maintains Protocol Compliance**: MS-RDPRFX specification doesn't define [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadata blocks[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Backward Compatible**: Legitimate RFX messages don't use metadata blocks[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Preserves Existing Logic**: All standard RFX processing remains intact[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Preserves Existing Codebase Logic[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All standard RFX block handlers remain unchanged [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSYNC, CODEC_VERSIONS, CHANNELS,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCONTEXT, FRAME_BEGIN, REGION, EXTENSION, FRAME_END[0m[1;39m)[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- State machine flow is preserved for legitimate messages[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Encoding functions continue to work unchanged[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Decoding of standard RFX messages unaffected[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Error handling and validation logic intact[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Addresses the Evaluation Report[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe crash occurs because:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Fuzzer sends random data that triggers the malicious code path[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Random blockOffset creates invalid target address [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0x7f3e07b98e20[0m[1;39m)[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Metadata handler attempts write to invalid address[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. AddressSanitizer detects SEGV on wild-addr-write[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix prevents this by:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Removing the code that reads blockOffset/metadataData[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Removing the arbitrary write operation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Either rejecting or ignoring WBT_METADATA blocks[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Eliminating the vulnerability entirely[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Side Effect**: Messages containing WBT_METADATA blocks will be rejected.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Mitigation**: This is desired behavior since:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No legitimate RFX encoder generates these blocks[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- They're not part of the MS-RDPRFX specification[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Only attack payloads would contain them[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Proper error logging will indicate why the message was rejected[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Side Effect**: [0m[3;35mNone[0m[39m for legitimate RFX traffic.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Mitigation**: Not needed - the removed code is not part of the standard protocol.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Conclusion[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis fix strategy completely removes malicious code that creates an arbitrary write[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability. The approach is safe because:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The removed code has no legitimate purpose[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No standard RFX functionality depends on it[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fix only affects malformed/attack inputs[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All existing tests using legitimate RFX messages will continue to pass[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m59[0m[39m: * The quantization values control the compression rate and quality. The value[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m60[0m[39m: * range is between [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m15[0m[39m. The higher value, the higher compression rate[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m61[0m[39m: * and lower quality.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m62[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1321[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m                                 [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m&context->expectedDataBlockType[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1322[0m[39m:   [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mbreak;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe compilation failure occurs because the previous patch removed the global [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvariable declarations [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`metadataBlock` and `metadataData`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but failed to remove all[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode that references these variables. Specifically:[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m142[0m[39m**: Global variable `metadataBlock` declaration was removed ✓[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m179[0m[39m**: Global variable `metadataData` declaration was removed ✓[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Lines [0m[1;36m674[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m680[0m[39m**: Code in `rfx_process_message_frame_begin` that reads and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodifies these variables was NOT removed ✗[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Lines [0m[1;36m709[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m736[0m[39m**: The `rfx_process_message_metadata` function [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontaining line [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m734[0m[39m with the write operation[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m still exists[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Lines [0m[1;36m1319[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1322[0m[39m**: WBT_METADATA case was modified to reject the block ✓[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe error at line [0m[1;36m727[0m[39m in the compilation log corresponds to the code that was [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginally at line [0m[1;36m734[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`*[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmetadataBlock = metadataData;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. However, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthere's also code at lines [0m[1;36m674[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m680[0m[39m in `rfx_process_message_frame_begin` that [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreferences these removed variables, which would also cause compilation errors.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Core Insights[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFrom the code analysis:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Security Vulnerability**: The metadata processing code implements an arbitrary[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory write primitive:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `metadataBlock` initialized to `&explicit_bzero` [0m[1;39m([0m[39ma libc function address[0m[1;39m)[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stream data controls both the target address offset and the value to write[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This is a classic exploit primitive allowing arbitrary memory writes[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Not Part of Specification**: [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `rfx_write_message_frame_begin` function writes only [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mframeIdx + [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnumRegions[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The metadata reading code attempts to read [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m additional bytes not in the spec[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No legitimate RFX encoding functions write WBT_METADATA blocks[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Comments reference MS-RDPRFX specification sections but never mention metadata[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Complete Removal Needed**:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All metadata-related code must be removed[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `rfx_process_message_metadata` function should be gutted or removed[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The extra reads in `rfx_process_message_frame_begin` must be deleted[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - WBT_METADATA blocks should be rejected at the dispatch level[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix must be applied to the **initial codebase** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbefore any patches[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, removing [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mall malicious metadata-related code:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Remove Global Variable Declarations[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **File**: `libfreerdp/codec/rfx.c`[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Line [0m[1;36m142[0m[39m**: Remove `UINT64 metadataBlock = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m&explicit_bzero;`[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Line [0m[1;36m179[0m[39m**: Remove `UINT64 metadataData = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Replace with comments indicating removal of malicious variables[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Remove Metadata Reading Code in rfx_process_message_frame_begin[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **File**: `libfreerdp/codec/rfx.c`[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Lines [0m[1;36m674[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m680[0m[39m**: Remove the entire conditional block that reads metadata from [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe stream:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```c[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mStream_GetRemainingLength[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m >= [0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m)[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      UINT64 blockOffset = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT64[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, blockOffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT64[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, metadataData[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      metadataBlock += blockOffset;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This code is not part of the legitimate TS_RFX_FRAME_BEGIN structure[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The spec defines only [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m bytes: frameIdx [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + numRegions [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m: Gut rfx_process_message_metadata Function[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **File**: `libfreerdp/codec/rfx.c`[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Lines [0m[1;36m709[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m736[0m[39m**: Keep the function signature but remove the malicious logic[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Replace the function body to immediately log an error and return FALSE[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This prevents the arbitrary write at line [0m[1;36m734[0m[39m: `*[0m[1;39m([0m[39mUINT64*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mmetadataBlock = [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmetadataData;`[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Keep the function declaration to avoid affecting other parts of the codebase that[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmight reference it[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Step [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m: Reject WBT_METADATA Blocks[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **File**: `libfreerdp/codec/rfx.c`[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Lines [0m[1;36m1319[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1322[0m[39m**: Modify the WBT_METADATA case in the switch statement[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Instead of calling `rfx_process_message_metadata`, log an error and set ok = [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFALSE[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Error message: [0m[32m"WBT_METADATA blocks are not supported and not part of MS-RDPRFX [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mspecification"[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Implementation Details[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### For rfx_process_message_metadata [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m709[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m736[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mReplace the entire function body with:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstatic INLINE BOOL [0m[1;35mrfx_process_message_metadata[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRFX_CONTEXT* WINPR_RESTRICT [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontext,[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                                RFX_MESSAGE* WINPR_RESTRICT [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmessage,[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                                wStream* WINPR_RESTRICT s,[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                                                UINT16* WINPR_RESTRICT [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpExpectedBlockType[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext->priv[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mWINPR_UNUSED[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmessage[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mWINPR_UNUSED[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mWINPR_UNUSED[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpExpectedBlockType[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mWLog_Print[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext->priv->log, WLOG_ERROR, [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[32m"WBT_METADATA blocks are not supported and not part of MS-RDPRFX [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mspecification"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return FALSE;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### For WBT_METADATA case [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1319[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1322[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcase WBT_METADATA:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mWLog_Print[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcontext->priv->log, WLOG_ERROR,[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[32m"WBT_METADATA blocks are not supported and not part of MS-RDPRFX [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mspecification"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    ok = FALSE;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    break;[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Optimal Approach**: Complete removal of all metadata-related code is the only [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecure solution. Partial removal leaves vulnerabilities or compilation errors.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Preserves Existing Logic**: [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fix only removes malicious code that was never part of the legitimate RFX [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprotocol[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No legitimate functionality depends on metadata processing[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The state machine [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexpectedDataBlockType[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m continues to work correctly[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All other block types [0m[1;39m([0m[39mWBT_FRAME_BEGIN, WBT_REGION, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are unaffected[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Addresses All Issues**:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fixes the compilation errors by removing all references to deleted variables[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Eliminates the arbitrary write vulnerability[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rejects WBT_METADATA blocks that should never appear in legitimate RFX streams[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Prevents the AddressSanitizer crash[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **No Side Effects**:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - WBT_METADATA is never written by encoding functions[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No test cases rely on metadata processing[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The rfx_write_message_frame_begin function proves metadata is not part of the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwire format[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Legitimate RFX streams will never contain WBT_METADATA blocks[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Similar Solutions**: The codebase already rejects unknown block types in the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefault case of the switch statement [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m1329[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1332[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, returning FALSE and logging[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man error. This fix applies the same pattern to WBT_METADATA.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Breaking Metadata-Dependent Code**: [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Risk**: Low - No legitimate code should depend on this malicious [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: The fuzzer and test suite will verify no regressions[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Function Signature Changes**:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Risk**: [0m[3;35mNone[0m[39m - We keep the function signature intact, just gut the [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimplementation[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: By keeping `rfx_process_message_metadata` as a stub, we avoid [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbreaking any forward declarations or function pointers[0m                              [2m                [0m
